    public interface Invocable<T>
    Describes the invoke methods of none task vAPI operation.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      CompletionStageFuture<T> invoke()
      Asynchronous method.
      CompletionStageFuture<T> invoke(InvocationConfig invocationConfig)
      Asynchronous method with InvocationConfig.

    • Method Detail

      • invoke

        CompletionStageFuture<T> invoke()
        Asynchronous method. Result of the invocation will be returned as a CompletionStageFuture. Once the server returns a value the future will be completed. If the operation invocation throws an exception then the CompletionStageFuture will complete exceptionally.
        Returns:
        CompletionStageFuture which holds the result of the operation invocation.

      • invoke

        CompletionStageFuture<T> invoke(InvocationConfig invocationConfig)
        Asynchronous method with InvocationConfig. Result of the invocation will be returned as a CompletionStageFuture. Once the server returns a value the future will be completed. If the operation invocation throws an exception then the CompletionStageFuture will complete exceptionally.
        Parameters:
        invocationConfig - used for the operation invocation.
        Returns:
        CompletionStageFuture which holds the result of the operation invocation.
